with activ_t as (

    select *,
           case when invested_companies >= 100 then 'high_activity'
                when invested_companies >= 20 then 'middle_activity'
                else 'low_activity'
            end as activity
       from fund)

select activity, round(avg(investment_rounds)) as round_count
  from activ_t
 group by activity
 order by round_count;
activity round_count

with pivot as (

    select people.id as id, education.instituition as inst_num
      from people
     inner join education
             on people.id = education.person_id
     where company_id in (

         select company.id
           from company
           left join funding_round
                  on company.id = funding_round.company_id
          where company.status = 'closed'
            and funding_round.is_first_round = 1
            and funding_round.is_last_round = 1))

select id, count(inst_num)
  from pivot
 group by id;

select fund.name as name_of_fund,
       company.name as name_of_company,
       funding_round.raised_amount as amount
  from investment
 inner join company
         on company.id = investment.company_id
 inner join fund
         on fund.id = investment.fund_id
 inner join funding_round
         on funding_round.id = investment.funding_round_id
 where company.milestones > 6
   and extract(year from funding_round.funded_at) between 2012 and 2013;

select buyer.name as buyer_name,
       acquisition.price_amount,
       seller.name as seller_name,
       seller.funding_total,
       round(acquisition.price_amount / seller.funding_total) as koef
  from acquisition
 inner join company as seller
         on seller.id = acquisition.acquired_company_id
 inner join company as buyer
         on buyer.id = acquisition.acquiring_company_id
 where acquisition.price_amount != 0
   and seller.funding_total != 0
 order by acquisition.price_amount desc, seller_name
 limit 10;

with usa_funds as (

    select extract(month from funding_round.funded_at) as month,
           count(distinct fund.name) as fund_num
      from investment
     inner join fund
             on fund.id = investment.fund_id
     inner join funding_round
             on funding_round.id = investment.funding_round_id
     where fund.country_code = 'USA'
       and extract(year from funding_round.funded_at) between 2010 and 2013
     group by month),

sales as (

    select extract(month from acquired_at) as month,
           count(acquired_company_id) as company_count,
           sum(price_amount) as total_amount
      from acquisition
     where extract(year from acquired_at) between 2010 and 2013
     group by month)

select usa_funds.month,
       usa_funds.fund_num,
       sales.company_count,
       sales.total_amount
  from usa_funds
  left join sales
         on usa_funds.month = sales.month;
month fund_num company_count total_amount

with year_2011 as (

    select country_code, avg(funding_total) as year_2011
      from company
     where extract(year from founded_at) = 2011
     group by country_code),

year_2012 as (

    select country_code, avg(funding_total) as year_2012
      from company
     where extract(year from founded_at) = 2012
     group by country_code),

year_2013 as (

    select country_code, avg(funding_total) as year_2013
      from company
     where extract(year from founded_at) = 2013
     group by country_code)

select year_2011.country_code,
       year_2011.year_2011,
       year_2012.year_2012,
       year_2013.year_2013
  from year_2011
 inner join year_2012
         on year_2011.country_code = year_2012.country_code
 inner join year_2013
         on year_2011.country_code = year_2013.country_code
 order by year_2011 desc;
